Still smiling at her, he took flight. His metal, jet-like wings made 
him soar through the sky. Heading high up, he took some time to feel 
the wind on his face. After staying still in the sky for a moment, he 
came back down fast. He broke his fall near the treetops. Finding 
Mistra again, he decided to ask some questions. The emotions he felt 
in her motivated him to continue.

AzureBlade: Mistra! Over here! (he came down lower, but was still in 
middair) Can I ask you something? What do you remember about yourself?

--- In nbwrpg@y..., HanaKirei85@a... wrote:
> <<> AzureBlade stepped outside the cave and into the forest. The sun 
was 
> > high in the sky, and a few clouds were crawling westwards. He 
> > stretched his wings, made of metal. He then turned to Mistra, and, 
> > even though she must have looked grotesque to another bot, she 
seemed 
> > beautiful to him. He had never felt that way. After the atrocities 
he 
> > had commited at the capture of his brother and the slaughter of 
the 
> > two Decepticons, this feeling was a bliss. He was feeling peaceful 
> > just looking at her.
> > 
> > AzureBlade: I know you will be able! If you need help however, I'm 
> > sure I'll be able to carry you to the city!>>
> 
> Mistra stepped out into the sunlight, enjoying the bright sunlight. 
A bit 
> odd, considering her beast form was partially a creature who 
preferred the 
> dark. Then again, she wasn't truely a bat, was she? With a stretch 
of her 
> own, she unfolded her own wings and smiled again at Azure. Hopefully 
he 
> didn't mind her company much...especially since she liked having him 
around 
> when it came down to it. And he was the only one she knew or trusted 
by now.
> 
> "Thank you Azure..." she said softly, smiling still.
